ANTHRAX - BANGLADESH: (RAJSHAHI) HUMAN, BOVINE
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 1 Apr 2014
Source: New Age [edited]
http://www.newagebd.com/detail.php?date=2014-04-01&nid=88498


At least 14 anthrax-infected patients were detected at village Raghunathpur of Raiganj upazila in Sirajganj [District, Rajshahi Division] Sunday evening [30 Mar 2014].

They are HB, 35, wife of HnA; SK, 40, wife of HdA; HM, 35; SK, 50, wife of AH; CK, 40, wife of ANH; NH, 35; JK, 22; MH, 26; SH, 32; MA, 50; AH, 50; PK, 18, daughter of AA; AK, 60; and RK, 8, daughter of TA.

Sirajganj civil surgeon Main Uddin Mia and his sanitary inspector Mohammad Ali Zinnah said [these villagers] were infected during slaughtering and preparing the meat of an anthrax-affected cow of Shaheb Ali of village Raghunathpur on [15 Mar 2014]. However, symptoms of the disease were noticed after 13 days.

The district health department as well as the upazila Prani Shampad department treated them locally, while HK was admitted to Bogra Medical College and Hospital in a critical condition.

A medical team from the health directorate in Dhaka had already visited the village, they added.

--
