[Our thanks to Mat for this report. I gather from Mat that an investigation team is due to visit the village shortly to investigate this outbreak, and collect soil and feed samples.

It is interesting that the owner of the sick and butchered cow is not listed among the sick. Otherwise the age range of the afflicted is very much as expected, with 4 of the 13 adults being wives. Children are not so often noted but they help out and carry meat home, and thus on occasion become infected. The lack of children in these events reflect a lack of exposure, not an age resistance. "HK" does not appear among the listed patients and so is either a 15th case or one of the women listed under a different name.

For a map of Sirajganj district, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sirajganj_District. For Bangladesh, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/txu-pclmaps-oclc-742924775-bangladesh_pol-2011.jpg. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2381105,10080.]
